Natural Remedies

{/* Cramps Section */}

Remedies for Cramps

  • Warm Compress: Apply a heating pad or warm water bottle to your lower abdomen.
  • Ginger Tea: Drink ginger tea with honey to reduce inflammation and pain.
  • Yoga Poses: Practice gentle yoga poses like child's pose and cat-cow stretch.
  • Essential Oils: Use lavender or peppermint oil for aromatherapy.
{/* Back Pain Section */}

Back Pain Relief

  • Massage: Gentle massage with warm sesame oil can help relieve back pain.
  • Heat Therapy: Use a heating pad on your lower back.
  • Stretching: Simple back stretches and exercises.
  • Herbal Remedies: Try turmeric tea or cinnamon tea.
{/* Diet Tips Section */}

Best & Worst Foods for Periods

{/* Best Foods & Drinks */}

✅ Best Foods & Drinks

  • Water & Hydrating Fruits (watermelon, cucumber) – Prevent bloating & headaches.
  • Leafy Greens (spinach, kale) – Boost iron levels & reduce fatigue.
  • Ginger & Turmeric – Help with cramps, nausea & inflammation.
  • Protein-Rich Foods (chicken, fish, lentils, beans, tofu) – Keep you strong & energized.
  • Dark Chocolate & Nuts – Reduce mood swings & cravings.
  • Yogurt & Kombucha – Support gut health & prevent infections.
  • Peppermint Tea – Relieves cramps & digestion issues.
{/* Foods to Avoid */}

❌ Foods to Avoid

  • Salty & Sugary Foods – Cause bloating & mood swings.
  • Caffeine (Coffee, Tea, Soda) – Triggers headaches & dehydration.
  • Alcohol – Worsens cramps & digestion issues.
  • Spicy Foods – May cause stomach pain & nausea.
  • Red Meat – Can increase cramps.
